mechanism:
Add a shared 3-phase attack clock that lives entirely inside trollAI (client-cosmetic, no server/onHit timing change). State fields to add in makeMonster's m={...} literal (around line 2017, next to atkCd): m.atkPhase=0 (0=idle, >0=running normalized 0..1 progress is derived), m.atkT=0 (seconds elapsed in current attack), m.atkDur=0 (total seconds for this attack), m.atkHit=false (did onHit fire yet), m.lungeBase=null (saved {x,z} of g.position before the strike lunge), m.atkKind=null. 

Helper to add just above meleeAttack (line 2753): 
  const startAtk=(dur,kind)=>{ if(m.atkPhase>0) return false; m.atkPhase=0.0001; m.atkT=0; m.atkDur=dur; m.atkHit=false; m.atkKind=kind; m.lungeBase={x:p.x,z:p.z}; return true; };
  const lunge=(amt)=>{ if(!m.lungeBase) return; p.x=m.lungeBase.x+(dx/d)*amt; p.z=m.lungeBase.z+(dz/d)*amt; }; // amt is + toward player; call with the per-phase value each frame so it interpolates, restore by lunge(0) on recovery
  const endAtk=()=>{ m.atkPhase=0; m.atkKind=null; if(m.lungeBase){ p.x=m.lungeBase.x; p.z=m.lungeBase.z; m.lungeBase=null; } };

REPLACE meleeAttack with a per-type version. New meleeAttack(kind, dur, onHit) advances the clock and runs the kind's pose function each frame:
  const meleeAttack=(kind,dur,onHit)=>{ if(m.atkPhase<=0){ m.atkCd-=dt; if(m.atkCd>0){ // not yet ready: hold a relaxed guard, let walk baseline ease back
        m.arms.L.rotation.x=lerp(m.arms.L.rotation.x,0.5,0.15); m.arms.R.rotation.x=lerp(m.arms.R.rotation.x,0.5,0.15); return; }
        if(!startAtk(dur,kind)) return; }
    m.atkT+=dt; const u=Math.min(1,m.atkT/m.atkDur); m.atkPhase=u; ATK[kind](m,u,dx,dz,d,lunge); // ATK[kind] writes absolute pose for the joints it owns
    if(!m.atkHit && u>=ATK_HITFRAC[kind]){ m.atkHit=true; if(player.pos.y-1.7 < p.y+1.9*m.scale){ onHit(); } else { m.atkCd=0.4; m.atkPhase=0; m.atkKind=null; lunge(0); m.lungeBase=null; return; } } // vertical-range gate preserved from old code
    if(u>=1){ endAtk(); } };

ATK is a per-kind lookup table of pose functions keyed by a phase u in [0,1] internally split into windup/strike/recovery sub-ranges via remap(u,a,b)=clamp((u-a)/(b-a),0,1). ATK_HITFRAC[kind] is the u at which the strike connects (onHit/damage fires there). Each pose fn writes ONLY absolute values to the joints it owns (arms.L/R rotation.x/y/z, torso.rotation.x/z, head.rotation.x, legs.L/R.rotation.x, g.scale, and lunge()); it never touches a joint another phase will not reset. Because meleeAttack returns early while m.atkPhase>0, walkAnim() is naturally skipped during the swing (the existing case bodies only call walkAnim in the d>range branch; in the attack branch we now never call it). Ranged types (shaman/spitter) keep their existing fire branches but get their windup poses driven by remapping their existing timers (m.casting/T.castWind, m.rangedTimer) into the same ease curves — no atkPhase needed for them since they already own their joints during the timer window.
